parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Overheating due to Faulty Head Gasket/Profile Gasket
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause severe damage to the engine head, leading to costly repairs, and potentially resulting in engine failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the handbrake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unintentionally, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or damage to property.
symptoms: The handbrake slips or does not hold
the vehicle rolls or moves even when the handbrake is engaged
the handbrake needs to be adjusted periodically due to slippage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to shift properly can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the transmission.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift from one gear to another
the vehicle gets stuck in a gear
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leaks from Upper Return Lines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks from the upper return lines can cause fuel to spill onto the engine and surrounding areas, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: fuel droplets or puddles under the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress into Control Box Causing Fuel Injector Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the control box can cause the fuel injector to malfunction, leading to fuel leaks and potentially causing a fire or explosion.
symptoms: warning lights or error messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the vehicle can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, especially when stopping or slowing down.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when coming to a stop
the vehicle starts right up again after stalling
the vehicle operates normally for a period of time before stalling again
the stalling issue may occur days later.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Locking and Engine Starting Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locking system and engine starting system can cause the driver to become trapped inside the vehicle, leading to a safety risk.
symptoms: the driver is unable to exit the vehicle
the sunroof must be opened to escape.
